FT  25 FEB 93 / Observer: Old flavour
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A few years ago Canada replaced the one-dollar bank note with a coin which
has become known as a 'Looney', as the Loon, a bird, is depicted on the
reverse. Now there's talk of introducing a two-dollar coin.
Will this mark the re-appearance of the doubloon?
