FT  25 FEB 93 / Technology: Company Snapshot - L &amp; P
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPANY SNAPSHOT:  Linklaters &amp; Paines is an international commercial law
firm, with headquarters in the City of London and offices in Brussels,
Paris, Frankfurt, New York, Hong Kong, Singapore and Tokyo.
NATURE OF BUSINESS:  Commercial law.  The firm's main areas of practice are
corporate and commercial, international finance and banking, commercial
property, litigation, tax and intellectual property.
EMPLOYEES:  1,600 staff, of whom 700 are lawyers.  Key personnel:  Barry
Dean, head of Know-How systems; Andrew Taylor, head of IT; Jeremy Parr,
Solicitor.
TECHNOLOGY FILE
SOFTWARE:  Kinesis Total Recall software is the basis of the Cormaks system
and two others delivering information on international finance and the
Financial Services Act.  Total Recall supports a combination of text and
data to diverse and disparate information, linked by subject area.
It does this by integrating the BRS/Search text retrieval package (from BRS
Software Products) into the Ingres relational database. Total Recall works
with all the big relational databases and free-text products.
Kinesis of Swindon developed the Total Recall information delivery software,
and installed the first Know-How system, Cormaks, two years ago.  Consultant
was Peter Attwood.
OTHER SYSTEM:  Currently running on a Wang 2200 network are several other
information banks, soon to be converted to Kinesis software: Cartel ofr
competition law.  Perks for employee benefits, Landmark for property, Planet
for environmental law, Clicks for litigation.
HARDWARE:  Kinesis uses a PC front-end to a sun SPARCserver.
VALUE OF SOFTWARE:  The original development contract with Kinesis was in
the region of Pounds 250,000, including software and consultancy, but
excluding hardware, and licences for BRS/Search and Ingres.
