</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE COMMONS social security committee plans to examine the handling of the
pension funds of a number of formerly state-owned companies, as part of an
inquiry into the government's plans for the pension funds of
soon-to-be-privatised businesses.
Harland &amp; Wolff, the Belfast shipbuilder, Swan Hunter, its Tyneside
counterpart, and National Bus Company are among the once public-sector
entities whose pension funds the cross-party body plans to look at.
