<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 93 / Rise in executive job offers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE PERCENTAGE of redundant executives receiving job offers is rising,
particularly in the south-east, Drake Beam Morrin, outplacement consultants,
says.
A total of 16 per cent of executives it counselled received offers in the
first four weeks of the year - up from 10 per cent last year. In the
south-east the proportion rose from 9 per cent to 18 per cent and in the
Midlands from 10 per cent to 17.6 per cent.
