<HEADLINE>
FT  25 FEB 93 / Renault continues Daf project
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RENAULT, the French vehicle maker, confirmed yesterday that it would use
Leyland Daf, the collapsed commercial vehicle maker, as a sub-contractor in
developing a new heavy van range.
Renault and Daf started on the joint development of a new 2.5 tonnes to 4.2
tonnes van range, code-named Excel, in 1990. Renault has now acquired all
the industrial property rights for the range.
The development of the van will continue in Birmingham with the existing
team of 50 Renault engineering staff and will use 190 Leyland Daf
engineering staff on a sub-contract.
