Speculation had raged that Mr Patten would miss a self-imposed deadline and
postpone publication of the legislation scheduled by the end of this month
to allow negotiations with Beijing.
But the governor said the arrangements for local elections in 1994 and
legislative elections a year later, at the centre of the dispute, had to be
agreed this year.
Referring to Mr Sze's statement, he said: 'That's not an ultimatum. What it
is, is a statement of what is an administrative imperative.'
