<TEXT>
THE JAPANESE government had been on the verge of announcing plans to open
its rice market to imports last month, a senior trade official admitted
yesterday, writes Charles Leadbeater. They had been shelved once it became
clear the prospects for an early Uruguay Round agreement had faded.
