<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 93 / International Company News: Nobel Industries to sell defence
unit to Celsius
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SWEDEN'S Nobel Industries is selling its defence electronics activities and
related real estate to state-owned Celsius Industries in a SKr1.55bn
(Dollars 204m) deal which starts the process of broadening the ownership
structure in Celsius.
The move came as Nobel's shares were suspended on the Stockholm and
Copenhagen bourses pending a separate announcement today.
Nobel will receive SKr325m in shares in Celsius for an approximate stake of
10 per cent, which values the whole of the defence group - 100 per cent
state-owned - at SKr3.25bn. Two weeks ago, the government lined Celsius up
as its next privatisation candidate by saying it wanted to broaden the
group's ownership structure and obtain a share listing before the summer.
Celsius is buying NobelTech Systems and NobelTech electronics for SKr755m,
and real estate amounting to SKr800m.
The purchase will give the companyan estimated 50 per cent share of the
country's defence industry. Mr Olle Lund, Celsius chairman and chief
executive, said: 'The acquisition of NobelTech further enhances our position
as one of Europe's leading defence industry groups, especially important
with respect to export markets.'
