Finland's parliament yesterday pledged unlimited financial assistance to
ensure the country's banks can meet their commitments, writes Christopher
Brown-Humes in Stockholm.
US credit rating agency Standard &amp; Poor's recently questioned Finland's
political will to tackle its banking crisis and the agency placed a number
