<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 93 / Austria output falls by 8.2%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   VIENNA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Industrial output in Austria during December fell 8.2 per cent, confirming
indications the economy lost momentum late last year, writes Ian Rodger in
Vienna.
In November, industrial production was down 2 per cent year on year,
according to the government's statistical office.
In December, the Austrian Institute of Economic Research (WIFO) revised down
its forecast of economic growth for 1993 from 2 per cent to 1.3 per cent; a
WIFO official said this week that it would have to be revised downward
again, perhaps to 1 per cent.
