<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 93 / World Stock Markets: America
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AFTER a third consecutive decline in 1992, US corporate profits are forecast
to hit new heights in 1993 and 1994.
IBES, which tracks and collates analysts' forecasts, says that S &amp; P 500
earnings on this basis are expected to increase by 23.4 per cent this year,
to Dollars 28.76 a share, and by another 18.6 per cent to Dollars 34.12 in
1994.
Gains for the Dow components are expected to be 31.1 per cent, and 22.7 per
cent respectively.
