<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 93 / International Company News: Loan losses hit Bank of Montreal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A FURTHER climb in loan losses caused Bank of Montreal's first-quarter
earnings to dip by 5 per cent, despite strong growth in mortgage and
commercial loans.
Earnings dropped CDollars 155m (USDollars 124m), or CDollars 1.12 a share,
in the three months to January 31, from CDollars 164m, or CDollars 1.23 a
share, a year earlier. Return on common equity fell to 12.5 per cent from
15.1 per cent.
Net interest income climbed to CDollars 764m from CDollars 744m, helped by
the receipt of CDollars 29m in overdue interest from Brazil. But this
improvement was offset by a 30 per cent jump in loan loss provisions to
CDollars 162m.
The bank said it expected loan losses for fiscal 1993 as a whole to total
CDollars 650m, up from CDollars 550m last year and almost double the figure
for 1991.
The latest figure includes a general provision of CDollars 100m for hitherto
unidentified losses.
