<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Admiral advances to Pounds 3.99m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Admiral, the Surrey-based computing services company, returned profits
before tax of Pounds 3.99m for 1992, a 15 per cent increase on the previous
Pounds 3.47m, despite intensifying competition and a commercial environment
showing no signs of improvement.
Turnover rose from Pounds 26.1m to Pounds 30.9m. Earnings per share were
24.2p (21.9p); a final dividend of 3.7p is recommended for a total of 5.4p.
Mr Clay Brendish, chairman, said the company had performed well in all its
business areas, although the emphasis had changed markedly. Financial
services constituted the company's largest market, accounting for 34 per
cent of turnover, but the proportion of business coming from the commercial
and industrial sectors doubled to 22 per cent.
</TEXT>
