<HEADLINE>
FT  24 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Multitrust
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Multitrust, an investment trust which concentrates its portfolio in smaller
UK companies and other investment trusts, had a net asset value of 35.25p
per share at the end of December.
The figure compared with 33.2p at the trust's June year-end and 35.64p at
the end of 1991. The value has risen by a further 9 per cent since the
latest year-end, according to Mr Andrew Perloff, chairman.
Earnings per share for the six months edged ahead to 1.46p (1.45p). The
interim dividend is maintained at 1.5p; a final of at least 1.2p is
forecast.
</TEXT>
