FT  24 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Hewitt ahead by 33%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GARY EVANS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A SUBSTANTIAL increase in activity in the final quarter enabled Hewitt
Group, the industrial ceramics and refractories maker, raise pre-tax profits
by 33 per cent from Pounds 625,000 to Pounds 832,000 in 1992.
Turnover rose 5 per cent to Pounds 7.76m. Earnings per share grew from 11.4p
to 14.8p, while a proposed final dividend of 1.75p makes a total for the
year of 3p (2.5p).
Mr David Heynes, chairman, said that after a relatively disappointing third
quarter there was a sharp improvement as a result of the devaluation of
sterling, together with certain customers increasing orders to rebuild their
stock to normal levels.
Considerable progress had been made at Hewitt's factories in Stoke-on-Trent
and Triptis, Germany. The Triptis factory will become fully operational in
mid-1993.
