FT  24 FEB 93 / Observer: Denway's debut
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Not hard to see who were the real winners in this week's Hong Kong stock
market debut of Denway Investments, the China 'concept' stock which was 657
times oversubscribed.
Denway itself ought to have made HKDollars 120m-HKDollars 150m simply from
the interest on owning the over-subscription funds for a week. Not bad,
given that it only forecast HKDollars 129m net profit for 1992.
Denway's main adviser, Peregrine, should have done nearly as well. As part
of the underwriting deal, it got to keep 3 per cent of the issue, which
could mean it will double the near HKDollars 50m in fees it has earned.
