FT  24 FEB 93 / Observer: Car-thartic
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sprechen Sie Deutsch? That is a question Jacques Calvet - Peugeot chairman,
Japan-basher extraordinaire, Maastricht opponent, etc, etc - prefers
officials from the Bank of France, at least, to answer in the negative.
He has two current bugbears. One is the Bundesbank's insularity in refusing
